caption.p: Genetic characterization of Tesano Aedes virus (TeAV). ( A) Genome structure showing VPg and internal ribosome entry site (IRES) at the 5′ terminal and a poly-A tail at the 3′ terminal. ( B) Genetic relationship between TeAV and other viruses of the family Iflaviridae. The maximum likelihood tree was constructed using the complete amino acid domain of the genome sequence with Genbank accession number LC496784. The amino acid domain was aligned using the MAFFT 7 online version [ 27]. Bootstrap support values from 1000 bootstrap replicates are indicated on the branches.
